<TITLE>Pillars of Eternity II was funded in one day</TITLE>
<TEXT>
Who needs a big publisher when you have the loyalty of fans? Obisidian's PC exclusive, Pillars of Eternity II: Deadfire, was funded in exactly 22 hours and 57 minutes. 9700 Fans raised the 1. million USD goal, and the money is still rolling in. At the time of writing, funding is at 140% of the initial goal and standing at $1,547,115 raised by fans. Obisidian is adding more characters to the game with further stretch goals. 
 
We have the best fans in the world. It is amazing how quickly they helped us reach the funding goal for Pillars of Eternity II: Deadfire . Our fans were responsible for the original games critical and financial success, and we are looking forward to doing it all over again with them for the sequel. For those who reserved Fig Game Shares, thank you for your trust in us and we look forward to having you share in the potential success of Pillars of Eternity II: Deadfire together, said Feargus Urquhart, CEO of Obsidian Entertainment. 
 
When Pillars of Eternity released in March 2015 it received praise from fans and critics alike with a current Steam review score of 9/10. Its success shows that there is a definite market for old-school, single-player, role-playing games. Pillars of Eternity is based on classic RPG's Baldur's Gate and Icewind Dale. 
 
